    public class AccountActivity
extends android.support.v7.app.AppCompatActivity

    AccountActivity

    The AccountActivity class takes data from the database and generate a list of countries. Every country is represented as checkboxes which the user can select depending on where he/she has traveled. The program then counts the amount of checked boxes and displays the total in the activity.

    • Method Detail

      • controlCheckBoxes

        public boolean controlCheckBoxes(DBCountry checkbox)
        Controls if a checkbox is selected or not by comparing the name of the checkbox (the country) with all components of the list containing all the user's visited countries which is stored in the database.
        Parameters:
        checkbox - the checkbox that is being controlled to see if the user has selected it
        Returns:
        true if the checkbox is selected by the user false if the checkbox is not selected by the user
        See Also:
        DBCountry

      • createCheckBoxes

        public void createCheckBoxes(java.util.List<DBCountry> countries)
        Method which creates and places checkboxes in the activity layout. The checkboxes represents countries which the user will be able to select to see how many countries he or she has visited.
        Parameters:
        countries - List of countries to be made in to checkboxes
        See Also:
        CheckBox, DBCountry, controlCheckBoxes(DBCountry)

      • checkOnClick

        public void checkOnClick(DBCountry country)
        OnClickListener for checkbox. When a checkbox is clicked on, this method sets the checkboxes status to either checked or unchecked depending on the previous status before the click. If the checkbox gets checked, this information is added to the database, otherwice it is deleted from the database. Every time a checkbox is checked or unchecked, the number of total visited countries is changed.
        Parameters:
        country - the checkbox which is being clicked on
        See Also:
        DBCountry, SQLiteHelper.deleteVisitedCountry(DBUser, DBCountry), SQLiteHelper.createVisitedCountry(DBUser, DBCountry), SQLiteHelper.getTotalVisitedCountries(DBUser)

      • createUnderline

        public void createUnderline()
        Method which creates an underline to the layout. It is used to delimit the title (continent) with its content (country).
